Theodore A. Shlapak: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 21, 2017 6:16 PM ET
Semiconductors and Semiconductor Equipment

Company Overview of ViXS Systems Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Theodore A. Shlapak  Director, ViXS Systems Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships73--
Background

		Mr. Theodore A. Shlapak, also known as Fred, serves as a Special Advisory on Technology Strategy of Gennum Corporation. Mr. Shlapak has more than 33 years of experience in the semiconductor industry Association. He served as the Chief Executive Officer, Semiconductor Products Sector of Motorola Solutions, Inc. from October 2002 to February 2004 and served as its President of Semiconductor Products Sector since September 2000. Mr. Shlapak served as an Executive Vice President ... of Motorola Solutions, Inc. from September 2000 to October 2002; Senior Vice President and Assistant to the President of SPS from December 1998 to September 2000; Senior Vice President and General Manager, SPS Wireless Subscriber Systems Group from June 1997 to December 1998. He joined Motorola in 1970 as an SPS applications engineer and in 1976 served as lead Tundra Semiconductor Corp.'s Canadian semiconductor operations. He later moved to Europe where he held roles of increasing responsibility, eventually leading Motorola's European semiconductor group in Switzerland. He served as Advisor to Board of Directors of Tundra Semiconductor Corp. since April 2004. He has been the Chairman and Director of SiGe Semiconductor, Inc. since June 27, 2007. He has been Director of ViXS Systems Inc. since February 23, 2017. He served as a Director of Applied Micro Circuits Corporation from May 19, 2006 to January 26, 2017. He has been an Independent Director of Gennum Corporation since May 2004. He served as a Director of Tundra Semiconductor Corp. since September 9, 2004. Mr. Shlapak holds B.Sc. and M.Sc. Degrees in Electrical Engineering from the University of Waterloo.Read Full Background




